Scan a PKGBUILD file or directory

Usage: aur-scan scan [OPTIONS] <PATH>

Arguments:
  <PATH>  Path to PKGBUILD or directory containing it

Options:
  -f, --format <FORMAT>      Output format [default: text] [possible values: text, json, sarif]
  -o, --output <OUTPUT>      Output file (stdout if not specified)
      --fail-on <FAIL_ON>    Exit with non-zero code if findings at or above this severity [possible values: critical, high, medium, low, info]
      --include-info         Include informational findings
  -c, --config <CONFIG>      Configuration file path
  -s, --severity <SEVERITY>  Minimum severity to report [possible values: critical, high, medium, low, info]
  -v, --verbose              Enable verbose output
  -q, --quiet                Quiet mode (only show findings)
  -h, --help                 Print help
